[2] Chile (Hualqui, Bio-Bio)
Date: Sun 7 Aug 2011
Source: Radio Bio-Bio [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2011/08/07/dos-persona-fallecieron-en-hualqui-por-virus-hanta-sin-que-aun-se-conozca-el-origen-del-contagio.shtml


In Hualqui [Concepcion province, Bio-Bio region], 2 people died due to
[a] hantavirus [infection], although the origin of the infection is
still unknown. This is a worrying health situation that affects the
neighbors in Hualqui. A 43-year-old man died in the Concepcion
Regional Hospital 23 days ago, where he was brought from Florida due
to evident respiratory complications. His widow is sure that he became
infected during his work repairing a road to the rural locality. Bad
news continued for the woman because on Friday [5 Aug 2011] her
brother-in-law, 33 years old, also died of [a] hantavirus
[infection].

Another 3 workers affected by the virus have been admitted to a
hospital in Penco [Concepcion province, Bio-Bio region].

[Byline: Nicole Villagra]

