[3] Chile (Cochamo, Los Lagos)
Date: Fri 12 Aug 2011
Source: El Repuertero [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.elrepuertero.cl/node/11708


A hantavirus infection takes a 2nd life in the Los Lagos region.
Although the results of the autopsy are awaited to confirm the cause
of death, the Base Hospital of Puerto Montt confirmed the death of a
resident from the Cochamo community [Llanquihue province, Los Lagos
region] from cardiorespiratory arrest.

Since May [2011], a plague of rodents has affected the inhabitants of
Palena province [Los Lagos region] and the Cochamo community.

[Byline: Felipe Chavez E]

