[4] Chile (national)
Date: Fri 12 Aug 2011
Source: Terra [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.terra.cl/actualidad/index.cfm?id_cat=302&id_reg=1708764


The Subsecretary of Public Health, Jorge Diaz, confirmed 39 hantavirus
infection cases nationally, a figure greater than was expected, which
obliged strengthening of preventive work of the Ministry of Health in
the areas of greatest risk in the country, from Maule to Aysen. The
background was given by Diaz during a visit to the biology laboratory
of the Institute of Public Health, during which time he said that last
year [2010], 61 cases of the disease occurred nationally.

According to the current epidemiological situation, the official
stated that, "it is expected that the same number of cases will be
repeated in 2011, classifying the situation as worrying, given the
high fatality rate of the virus [infection]."

In addition to reminding [everyone] of preventive measures (such as
storing food stuffs in closed containers; not leaving leftover food on
the table, furniture and floors; ventilation of closed spaces before
entering), Diaz assured that -- as preventive action -- the SEREMIs
[Secretaria Regional Ministerial de Salud; Regional Ministerial
Secretariat of Health] of the southern regions of the country were
instructed to redouble preventive actions, especially in areas
affected by the earthquake.

--
